pull_request.body:
[![Mend Renovate](https://app.renovatebot.com/images/banner.svg)](https://renovatebot.com)

This PR contains the following updates:

| Package | Change | Age | Adoption | Passing | Confidence |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| [jwt-decode](https://togithub.com/auth0/jwt-decode) | [`3.1.2` -> `4.0.0`](https://renovatebot.com/diffs/npm/jwt-decode/3.1.2/4.0.0) | [![age](https://developer.mend.io/api/mc/badges/age/npm/jwt-decode/4.0.0?slim=true)](https://docs.renovatebot.com/merge-confidence/) | [![adoption](https://developer.mend.io/api/mc/badges/adoption/npm/jwt-decode/4.0.0?slim=true)](https://docs.renovatebot.com/merge-confidence/) | [![passing](https://developer.mend.io/api/mc/badges/compatibility/npm/jwt-decode/3.1.2/4.0.0?slim=true)](https://docs.renovatebot.com/merge-confidence/) | [![confidence](https://developer.mend.io/api/mc/badges/confidence/npm/jwt-decode/3.1.2/4.0.0?slim=true)](https://docs.renovatebot.com/merge-confidence/) |

---

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>auth0/jwt-decode (jwt-decode)</summary>

### [`v4.0.0`](https://togithub.com/auth0/jwt-decode/blob/HEAD/CHANGELOG.md#Version-400)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/auth0/jwt-decode/compare/v3.1.2...v4.0.0)

[Full Changelog](https://togithub.com/auth0/jwt-decode/compare/v3.1.2..v4.0.0)

A new version of the library, including a couple of improvements:

-   No longer include a polyfill for [atob](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/atob), as this is [supported in all major browsers](https://caniuse.com/?search=atob) (and [node environments > 14](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/atob#browser_compatibility)).
-   Compile to ES2017, dropping support for anything that does not support ES2017 (which should be very limited [according to caniuse](https://caniuse.com/?search=es2017))
-   Use Node's atob when running on node.
-   Drop support for Node 14 and 16, add support for Node 20.
-   Add support for package.json's `exports` field, for better CJS/ESM support
-   Reorganize build artifacts for better CJS/ESM support (cjs and esm needs to be their own directory with a cjs specific package.json file)
-   Drop manual UMD bundle creation in `index.standalone.ts`, but rely on rollup instead.
-   Infer JwtPayload and JwtHeader default types from the `header` argument by using overloads.

**Additionally, this PR ensures the file size is decreased:**

-   **ESM and CJS decreased by 22%**
-   **UMD decreased by 37%**

Even though some users might experience breaking changes, mostly because of the `exports` field, the majority should be able to update without making any changes, assuming the SDK is used in environments with support for `atob`.

</details>

issue.title: v14
issue.body:
Feature branch for v14

https://github.com/UniversalMediaServer/UniversalMediaServer/issues/3969

**Done for now :**
fix scan button state
fix FileWatcher error logged on shutdown
fix sse with less blocker sync as log can block a lot
fix AudioTrackCount
fix multi renderer creation on webguiplayer
fix RELEASEDATE as timestamp
fix typo in column name

rebuild the store parser
moved chapter hls to hlshelper
renderers now have their own MediaStore
renderers now have their own globalids

implement database cache memory usage show
implement StoreResource clear children
implement GlobalIdRepo clear
implement Renderer resetRootFolder -> clear all children
delete rootfolder, etc. on renderer deletion

implement group authorization for shares
added iTunes, iPhoto and Aperture to SharedContent
implement user pin code
implement user avatar

implement user filestatus
now save the default mimetype
refactored library things from net.pms.dlna to net.pms.store
refactored DLNAResource -> StoreResource
added DidlHelper from old DLNAResource
added DlnaHelper from old DLNAResource
split store container / store item
merge LibraryScanner and MediaScanner -> StoreScanner

organize imports
code cleaning

added copy files status on each users for filling user status
some user want to keep it, others can reset it on the shared folder

implement RendererUser
removed cache option.
created thumbnail store

update h2 database to v2.222
remove apache httpcore dep
add thread name for debug

**UPnP :**
implement ContentDirectoryError
added systemUpdateId event (was never implemented)
partially added jupnp mediaserver didl results


**React app**
update mantine 6.0.21 -> 7.1.0
update web-vitals 3.4.0 -> 3.5.0
removed unnecessary deps

split home renderer/device as device ip hostname take long time
add loading on renderer screen
add loading on device screen
add loading on player renderer creation
change shared settings table to box (nicer)

fix breadcrumbs size
fix logs page

**This PR is awaiting testing and review**

Users can now choose to link a renderer to a user on the renderer gui.
That should enjoy users that want to hide some things for other (like for kids).
Also, as file status is now based on user, other viewers will not disturb user file status.

I forgot the user choice on upnp for now as it require too much to do.
Sad as it was a good idea on my head.

Fixes https://github.com/UniversalMediaServer/UniversalMediaServer/issues/1980
Fixes https://github.com/UniversalMediaServer/UniversalMediaServer/issues/980

comment.body:
> I see a lot of exceptions about unknown image format when scanning MP3s. I know I have a few problematic MP3s that have caused this in previous versions but this seems to be on all of them.

`MetadataExtractorParser` was not changed, so I doubt the result change from V13.
Here, their is no error in fact, but an advice that the file was not recognized as an image file, and it trace why.

Maybe this part will need to be changed to avoid parsing if it is not an image file.

For info, V14 will re scan each file as the `MediaInfo.Parser` field was introduced in V14, and the database was changed a lot introducing new fields.
